Sentencas: Three-dimensional (3D) microstructure of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes plays critical roles in determining fuel cell performance.
Titulo: In-situ quantification of solid oxide fuel cell electrode microstructure by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy

Sentencas: The state-of-the-art quantification technique such as X-ray computed tomography enables direct calculation of geometric factors by 3D microstructure reconstruction.
Titulo: In-situ quantification of solid oxide fuel cell electrode microstructure by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy

Sentencas: Taking advantages of in-situ, fast-responding and low cost, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy represented by distribution of relaxation time (DRT) is a novel technique to estimate geometric properties of fuel cell electrodes.
Titulo: In-situ quantification of solid oxide fuel cell electrode microstructure by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy

Sentencas: In this study, we employed the anode supported cells with the cell configuration of Ni-YSZ parallel to YSZ parallel to LSM-YSZ as an example and compared the tortuosity factor of pores of the anode substrate layer by X-ray computed tomography and DRT analysis.
Titulo: In-situ quantification of solid oxide fuel cell electrode microstructure by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy

Sentencas: Good agreement was found, validating the feasibility of in-situ microstructural quantification by using the DRT technique.
Titulo: In-situ quantification of solid oxide fuel cell electrode microstructure by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy
